The paper deals with hyperspectral image classification using neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and convolutional layers also suggests that the paper could belong to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also deals with spatial contextual features, which could suggest that it belongs to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
